        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We intend to image the distribution of the emission of the water H2O, v2=1 (1(1,0)-1(0,1) transition. Our ALMA-OT science goal will thus be achieved with 1 spectral window (1 baseband) of 468.75 MHz. In addition, we set one baseband of 1875.0 MHz for continuum purpose due to the line richness of source. 

Also, from SMA continuum observations carried out at 690 GHz by Beuther et al. (2006), we estimated that the continuum peak flux density should be about 0.18 Jy per beam.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to image the distribution of the emission of the water H2O, v2=1 (1(1,0)-1(0,1) transition toward the Orion-KL star forming region in band 9 using the C36-3 configuration, resulting into an angular resolution of 0.2''.

High angular resolution is required to spatially resolve the multiple kinematic components that are associated with the H2O emission seen within the Herschel beam. 

The maximum detectable source size being 2.8'', we seek to resolve the tiny water clump and to filter out the emission arising from the outflow.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to image the distribution of the emission of the water H2O, v2=1 (1(1,0)-1(0,1) transition toward Orion-KL.

We aim for a sensitivity of 190 mJy per beam which will give us, under nominal conditions (pwv of 1.262 mm) and according to our model which is based on our Herschel observations (Neill et al. 2013), a signal-to-noise ratio greater than 10. This requires a total observing time of 34.13 min.

Also, we ask for the high spectral resolution of 0.222 km/s in order to separate potential line blends.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
